---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import summary from '../../../proof/bakeoff/shared-core/summary.json';
import ledger from '../../../proof/bakeoff/shared-core/loc-boundary-ledger.json';
const components=['Button','Field','Tabs','Select','Dialog','Popover','Date Picker'];
const frameworks=['React','Vue','Svelte','Solid'];
---
<Layout title="Shared-core evidence · Kumo">
<header><p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Candidates</a> / Shared core</p><h1>Shared core: core-only evidence</h1><p>This candidate shares immutable behavior/ARIA contracts and reducers while retaining framework-native rendering, reactivity, and event binding. The evidence is deliberately labeled partial.</p></header>
<aside><strong>Zero browser targets passed.</strong> All 28 component/framework targets are <b>partial</b>. No target-native client build, SSR run, or real Chrome/CDP execution was performed.</aside>
<section class="stats"><article><strong>28</strong><span>partial targets</span></article><article><strong>116</strong><span>passed core/type/maintainability gates</span></article><article><strong>220</strong><span>not-run gates</span></article><article><strong>0</strong><span>browser targets</span></article></section>
<section><h2>Evidence matrix</h2><p>Passed entries concern separately exercised contracts, reducer behavior, static types, maintainability, or escape-hatch accounting. They are not target-browser evidence.</p><div class="table"><table><thead><tr><th>Component</th>{frameworks.map(f=><th>{f}</th>)}</tr></thead><tbody>{components.map(c=><tr><th>{c}</th>{frameworks.map(f=><td>partial</td>)}</tr>)}</tbody></table></div></section>
<section><h2>Reducer and contract boundary</h2><p><code>src/index.ts</code> and <code>src/views/native.ts</code> contain immutable behavior/ARIA contracts. Native React, Vue, Svelte, and Solid views own element creation/templates, reactive state, and event binding. Focus management and portals were excluded and remain not-run.</p><div class="table"><table><thead><tr><th>File</th><th>Boundary</th><th>Kind</th><th>LOC</th></tr></thead><tbody>{ledger.entries.map(e=><tr><td><code>{e.file}</code></td><td>{e.boundary}</td><td>{e.kind}</td><td>{e.loc}</td></tr>)}</tbody><tfoot><tr><th colspan="2">Measured totals</th><th>{ledger.totals.shared} shared</th><th>{ledger.totals.native} native</th></tr></tfoot></table></div></section>
<section class="removed"><h2>Synthetic evidence was removed</h2><p>Earlier synthetic DOM/browser claims were removed because they did not execute target-native output in a browser. Receipts now explicitly mark browser, DOM/ARIA, behavior, SSR, hydration, node preservation, package, network, and console categories <b>not-run</b> unless independently exercised. This prevents core reducer checks from being mistaken for framework integration proof.</p></section>
<section class="removed"><h2>Select pilot supersedes the aggregate matrix</h2><p>The current Select receipt is fail-closed: 8/8 model contract vectors pass, but Solid has observed interaction/hydration failures and React, Vue, and Svelte browser gates are blocked. Structural build or SSR success is not browser parity. Consumer DX is 3 passed / 22 blocked / 6 not-run.</p><p><a href="/select-pilot/">Read the receipt-derived Select comparison →</a></p></section>
<nav><a href="/bakeoff/">Compare all architecture candidates →</a></nav>
</Layout>
<style>header{max-width:850px;padding:32px 0 12px}h1{font-size:clamp(38px,5vw,58px);margin:8px 0;letter-spacing:-.04em}header>p:last-child,section>p{color:#475569;line-height:1.65}.eyebrow{font-size:12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em}aside,.removed{margin:24px 0;padding:18px 20px;border-left:4px solid #d97706;background:#fffbeb;line-height:1.6}.stats{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:10px;margin:34px 0}.stats article{padding:18px;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:9px;background:white}.stats strong{display:block;font-size:28px}.stats span{color:#64748b;font-size:12px}section{margin:38px 0}.table{overflow:auto;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:9px}table{width:100%;min-width:650px;border-collapse:collapse;background:white}th,td{padding:11px;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;text-align:left;font-size:13px}tbody td:not(:first-child){color:#92400e}tfoot{background:#f7f8fa}nav{margin:36px 0}@media(max-width:650px){.stats{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}</style>